 p = \frac{1}{12} 
 (1-p)p = \frac{1}{12}\times\frac{11}{12}=\frac{11}{12^2} 
 (1-p)^{n-1}p=\frac1{12}\times\left(\frac{11}{12}\right)^{n-1} 
 \begin{align} G(z) &= \sum_{n=1}^\infty P(X=n)z^n \\&= \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac1{12}\cdot\left(\frac{11}{12}\right)^{n-1} z^n \\&= \frac{z}{12} \sum_{n=1}^\infty \left(\frac{11z}{12}\right)^{n-1} \end{align} 
